rules.sql: SELECT COUNT(${default_file_name}) FROM (SELECT id, category, ROW_NUMBER() OVER (PARTITION BY category ORDER BY numeric_col), RANK() OVER (PARTITION BY category ORDER BY numeric_col), DENSE_RANK() OVER (PARTITION BY category ORDER BY numeric_col), PERCENT_RANK() OVER (PARTITION BY category ORDER BY numeric_col), CUME_DIST() OVER (PARTITION BY category ORDER BY numeric_col), NTILE(500) OVER (PARTITION BY category ORDER BY numeric_col), LAG(numeric_col, 10) OVER (PARTITION BY category ORDER BY id), LEAD(numeric_col, 10) OVER (PARTITION BY category ORDER BY id), FIRST_VALUE(numeric_col) OVER (PARTITION BY category ORDER BY numeric_col ROWS BETWEEN UNBOUNDED PRECEDING AND CURRENT ROW), LAST_VALUE(numeric_col) OVER (PARTITION BY category ORDER BY numeric_col ROWS BETWEEN CURRENT ROW AND UNBOUNDED FOLLOWING), SUM(numeric_col) OVER (PARTITION BY category ORDER BY id ROWS BETWEEN 500 PRECEDING AND 500 FOLLOWING) FROM stress_test_data WHERE id <= 1000000)
rules.description: Multiple complex window functions

rules.sql: SELECT category, status, priority, COUNT(${default_file_name}), SUM(numeric_col), AVG(numeric_col), MIN(numeric_col), MAX(numeric_col), STDDEV(numeric_col), VARIANCE(numeric_col), SUM(DISTINCT numeric_col), COUNT(DISTINCT numeric_col), MEDIAN(numeric_col), PERCENTILE_CONT(0.1) WITHIN GROUP (ORDER BY numeric_col), PERCENTILE_CONT(0.2) WITHIN GROUP (ORDER BY numeric_col), PERCENTILE_CONT(0.3) WITHIN GROUP (ORDER BY numeric_col), PERCENTILE_CONT(0.4) WITHIN GROUP (ORDER BY numeric_col), PERCENTILE_CONT(0.5) WITHIN GROUP (ORDER BY numeric_col), PERCENTILE_CONT(0.6) WITHIN GROUP (ORDER BY numeric_col), PERCENTILE_CONT(0.7) WITHIN GROUP (ORDER BY numeric_col), PERCENTILE_CONT(0.8) WITHIN GROUP (ORDER BY numeric_col), PERCENTILE_CONT(0.9) WITHIN GROUP (ORDER BY numeric_col) FROM stress_test_data WHERE id <= 1700000 GROUP BY category, status, priority HAVING COUNT(${default_file_name}) > 1000 ORDER BY SUM(numeric_col) DESC
rules.description: Complex aggregations with multiple levels

rules.sql: SELECT COUNT(${default_file_name}) FROM stress_test_data a CROSS JOIN stress_test_data b CROSS JOIN stress_test_data c WHERE a.id <= 2000 AND b.id <= 2000 AND c.id <= 2000 AND a.category = b.category AND b.status = c.status AND a.numeric_col BETWEEN b.numeric_col-2000 AND b.numeric_col+2000 AND b.numeric_col BETWEEN c.numeric_col-1000 AND c.numeric_col+1000 AND a.priority <= b.priority AND b.priority <= c.priority
rules.description: Multiple cross joins with filtering
